properties.name: spring.diamd.qpid.client-id
properties.description:
JMS clientID to use for connections. A clientID can only be used by one Connection at a time, so setting it
 will restrict the ConnectionFactory to creating a single open Connection at a time.

properties.name: spring.diamd.qpid.deserialization-policy.black-list
properties.description:
Blacklist of classes or packages. Blacklist overrides the whitelist, entries that could match both are
 counted as blacklisted.

properties.name: spring.diamd.qpid.password
properties.description: Login password of the AMQP broker.

properties.name: spring.diamd.qpid.receive-local-only
properties.description: Whether the client only checks its local message buffer when using receive calls with a timeout.

properties.name: spring.diamd.qpid.receive-no-wait-local-only
properties.description: Whether the client only checks its local message buffer when using receiveNoWait calls.

properties.name: spring.diamd.qpid.remote-url
properties.description: The URL of the remote peer the AMQP client should connect to.
